Kaduna &mdash; The National Commission for Refugees, Migrants and Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) yesterday said its ultimate goal is to end encampment of people in Nigeria.The Federal Commissioner of the Commission, Hajiya Sadiya Umar Farouq said this during the distribution of relief materials to IDPs in Kaduna.Items distributed to IDPs from the North-East and Southern Kaduna are rice, beans, Garri, salt, seasonings, cooking stove, Palm oil, vegetable oil, pomade, detergent, soap, mattress and notebooks, among others.